-- Polish mBank says sees one-off boost of $55 mln from AXA deal
-- By Marcin Goclowski
-- Fri Sep 12, 2014 03:19AM EDT
-- None



WARSAW, Sept 12 (Reuters) - Polish lender mBank <MBK.WA> said on Friday that the planned sale of its insurance arm to AXA <AXAF.PA> will increase its gross profit by 180 million zlotys ($55 million).

The French group agreed to buy mBank's insurance company BRE TUiR. MBank, the local unit of German Commerzbank <CBKG.DE>, has also signed a 10-year insurance distribution agreement with AXA. The whole deal is worth 135 million euros ($175 million).